    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of hardwood timber tree native from the Himalayas to the southern tip of India and on the island of Java in Indonesia. The foliage is used as fodder and the bark is used as a source of tannins extracted for medicinal purposes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
